(2) Smart Billing Slab (no nested if allowed)
Write a method:   double calculateBill(double amount, boolean isFirstOrder)

Rules (use only if – else, no nested if):
- If amount < 500 give no discount
- If amount ≥ 500 and < 1500  give 5% discount
- If amount ≥ 1500 give 10% discount
- If it is first order, give extra 2% discount on the final amount

You must combine conditions correctly without using nested if.
class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        boolean isFirstOrder=true;
        double amount=1490;
        Main obj=new Main();
        double finamt=obj.calculateBill(amount,isFirstOrder);
        System.out.println("The final amount: "+ finamt);
    }
    public double calculateBill(double amount,boolean isFirstOrder){
        double discount=0.0;
        if (amount<500){
            discount=0.0;
        }
        else if(amount>=500 && amount<1500){
            discount=0.05;
        }
        else if(amount>=1500){
            discount=0.1;
        }
        double finalamt=amount-(discount*amount);
        if (isFirstOrder){
            finalamt=finalamt-(0.02*finalamt);
        }
        return finalamt;
    }
}
(3) Bank Loan Approval Logic
Write a method:  String loanDecision(int age, int salary, int creditScore)

Rules using nested if–else:
 If age ≥ 21
    If salary ≥ 25000
         If creditScore ≥ 700  print Approved
         Else print Rejected – Low credit score
    Else print Rejected – Low salary
 Else print Rejected – Under age
class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int age=22;
        int salary=30000;
        int creditScore=750;
        Main obj=new Main();
        String result=obj.loanDecision(age, salary, creditScore);
        System.out.println(result);
    }
    public String loanDecision(int age, int salary, int creditScore){
        String res="";
        if (age>=21){
            if (salary>=25000){
                if (creditScore>=700){
                    res="Approved";
                }
                else{
                    res="Low credit score";
                }
            }
            else{
                res="Low salary";
            }
        }
        else{
            res="Under age";
        }
        return res;
    }
}
